The paper deals with the existence and complexity of approximate equilibria in congestion games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves analyzing the complexity of decision problems related to PNE, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of circuit gadgets suggests a connection to computational complexity theory and circuit complexity (cs.DS). The study of approximate equilibria involves optimization, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with congestion games, which is a specific area within game theory and economics (cs.EC).
